To prove the Holder inequality for general exponents, we can use the fact that for any $p, q \in [1, \infty)$ such that $\frac{1}{p} + \frac{1}{q} = \frac{1}{r}$, we can apply the Cauchy-Schwarz inequality to the functions $f^p$ and $g^q$ to get:

